{"session_id":"019f63a5-8545-7f70-9a3e-843d1a5fe8c5","turn_id":"019f63a5-89cc-77f0-bfb8-3dd69a75aa98","transcript_path":null,"cwd":"/Users/lawrence/fun/cmuxterm-hq/worktrees/feat-simulator-pane","hook_event_name":"Stop","model":"gpt-5.6-sol","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","stop_hook_active":false,"last_assistant_message":"{\"findings\":[{\"title\":\"Handle workspaceTodo in the extracted panel-title switch\",\"body\":\"This new switch is not exhaustive because `PanelType` includes `.workspaceTodo`, but the extracted helper omits that case. The file is included in the app target's Sources build phase, so the branch will fail to compile. Add the workspace-todo title handling already present in the original `ClosedItemHistory.swift` helper, or remove the duplicate extraction.\",\"priority\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.99,\"category\":\"bug\",\"code_location\":{\"file_path\":\"Sources/ClosedItemHistory+PanelTitle.swift\",\"line\":16}},{\"title\":\"Actually stop active Simulator work when the remote flag is disabled\",\"body\":\"Flipping the PostHog flag to false only replaces `SimulatorPanelView` with the disabled placeholder. Its `onDisappear` releases input and hides overlays, but does not stop the worker, camera injection, location route, capture/log sessions, or other coordinator-owned work; that cleanup exists in `SimulatorPaneCoordinator.close()`. Consequently the advertised active-pane kill switch can leave private-framework and camera activity running invisibly after the UI says the feature is disabled. The flag transition needs an explicit teardown or fully suspending lifecycle path for every active Simulator pane.\",\"priority\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.92,\"category\":\"bug\",\"code_location\":{\"file_path\":\"Sources/Panels/PanelContentView.swift\",\"line\":125}},{\"title\":\"Allow context and event-log reads when the Simulator is not streaming\",\"body\":\"The blanket streaming guard rejects `.context` and `.eventLog`, even though both cases later read coordinator state without contacting the streaming worker. This makes `cmux ios list` fail when any enumerated pane is restored, connecting, or failed, and prevents reading the event log precisely when diagnosing a failed worker. Exempt these coordinator-only reads from the streaming requirement while retaining the guard for operations that actually require a live stream.\",\"priority\":\"P2\",\"confidence\":0.96,\"category\":\"bug\",\"code_location\":{\"file_path\":\"Sources/TerminalController+ControlSimulatorOperations.swift\",\"line\":22}}],\"overall_correctness\":\"patch is incorrect\",\"overall_explanation\":\"The branch contains a compile-blocking non-exhaustive switch and two lifecycle/control defects: the remote kill switch does not terminate active Simulator work, and useful read-only commands are incorrectly unavailable outside the streaming state.\",\"overall_confidence\":0.98}"}